title: For Sale:  WWII M1 Carbine Standard Products, rare in mint condition 0 ME
postcontent:
Standard Products U.S. Cal. .30 M1 Carbine. Manufactured between March 1943 to September 1943.  Only 4.5%  of carbines made were Standard Products only Rock-O-La produced less.  These sell on Gunbroker for $1.200

 Carbine is in excellent condition with an excellent bore, with many early features.

 Please see photos of detailed parts. This is an original G.I. Carbine with no import marks.

 In early production Standard Products operated only as an assembly point. A great many parts were received from Inland, NPM, Rock Ola, Underwood and IBM. These parts included those produced by subcontractors for these installations.

 The Carbine was up graded with the adjustable rear sight and Flip Safety only. This is a excellent condition Carbine and would be very hard to up grade.

 Stock: RSG Saginaw Gear with nice cartouche

 Barrel: Underwood 8-43

 Barrel Band: Type 2A

 Hand Guard: 2 Rivet LWB: IBM

 Bolt: flat Quality Hardware

 Op Rod: Type III AOB: IBM
